1)	Introduction to CRM

Mark Benioff is the owner of Salesforce. Lunched in 1999 in cloud.
Salesforce.com is the company/Org developed by Mark Benioff and it is lunched the CRM that CRM toll is Salesforce.
In URL:  If URL start with below then the instance is from the that region of go to company profile to see the instance.
In Company profile we can be able to see the user licenses details like used licenses and available details.
 
Ap: Asia specific
Na: North America
Eu: Europe
For Sandbox environment for all locations ‘cs’ will be there in URL.
Production URL: login.salesforce.com
Sandbox URL:  test.salesforce.com
User id:
Naresh@salesforce.com-> production user
Naresh@salesforce.com.sandbox-> sandbox used id.

Multitenant environment
Multiple user using a single data base.
By using Salesforce.com org id it will different the organization data like dxc, Accenture like that and it will be available in organization profile and it will 15 digit unique.

Object ID:  if we click on the object then In URL we can find the Object id
Account: 001
Contact: 003
Lead:00Q
Record ID: It is 18 digit unique id. Object id(like account 001) +Record id 15 digit. 
15 digit id we can find in URL because of security reasons. If we want see the 18 digit id then go to the SOSQ query.

In Recycle, record will there for 15 days after that salesforce will delete permanently. 
New user activation URL will valid only for 7 days.
 

 

Application in SF: 
	It is a just like bucket where we puts tabs/ Functionalities/ do automation.
	An app in Salesforce is a set of objects, fields, and other functionality that supports a business process. You can see which app you’re using and switch between apps using the App Launcher ( App Launcher icon).
	Once we created App in Lightning Environment then we can’t use it Classis again we need to create it in Classic.
	While creating TAB we assigned to one Sales application only now we need to add this for service cloud also then use below path.
Classic:
              ---> Adminster-> Create -> Apps -> Select App and add the tab to App.
Lightning: 
	->Setup->Platform tools->Apps->App manger-> Select App and add the tab to App.
 Or click on the edit icon on the app.
 

To use images or documents in SF we need to upload first those in Documents folder.

	Schema Builder: it is used to see the relationship between the objects.
Through this we can create object, Fields.
Also we can be able to create a new objects and field layout. If created a field through schema builder we don’t have to option choose which page layout to assign. If create a fields through schema builder mandatory fields will be added to the object page layout but optional fields we need to add it manually.

	To enable Force.com Quick menu in classic go to Name-> my setting-> select Personal | Advanced User Detail and enable quick access menu.
