Trail head: Formulas & validations, Duplicate management.

->Formal fields:
 

 




Rollup Summary

	Rollup summary is used to summarize the corresponding child records.
	Roll up summary can be created only on the object which is already parent to the other object otherwise we can’t create. i.e master-details relationship only.
	Example. In Object ‘B’ we have created one Master detail field by choosing the master object    as ‘A’. Then we can create a Rollup summary field on Object ‘A’ not be able to create on ‘B’.
	We can perform the operations Count, Sum, Min and Max of the child record from all the records or we can specify the Filter(Condition).
	On a single object we create 25 rollup summary.

 

 

Validation Rules

	ISNEW() is the function to check whether it’s newly creating record or not.
	ISCHANGE(fieldname) function to identify the modify record.
	PRIORVALUE(fieldname) it will tell you the old value the field.
	
 

 
 



 


 
 
 




Duplicate Rules


	Duplicate Rules: First create matching rules and then create a duplicate rule.
	Matching rules and duplicate rules we need to activate it. When we activate Matching rules it will send email confirmation to the register email.
	By default Standard duplicate rules available for Account, Contact, Lead and   Persona Account. If we want we can create for Custom objects.
	Per object we use 5 active duplicate rules.
  
 


Relationships
We can see the relationship between the objects in Schema Builder and workbench.

1)	Master-detail relationship
2)	Lookup relation
3)	Junction object
4)	Hierarchical
5)	External relation
Master-detail relation ship


 

Sharing Settings
 
 

	In Sharing setting: read Only option selected then If User who has  read permission on the master object they can create/Edit and delete the child records. In above example Sam, Ram and Faraz.
	In Sharing setting: Read/Write option selected then If User who has Read/Write permission on the master object they can create/Edit and delete the child records. In above example Faraz.
 

 


 


 

 

 


 


 


Lookup relationship

 

 
	Look up is loosely couple relation.
	While creating Lookup Relationship field if we enable Clear value, Then it will allow to delete the parent record and replace the value with blank.
	While creating Lookup Relationship field if we enable Don’t allow deletion, Then it will not allow to delete the parent record.
	If you want to create a master detail field on the object which is already having the data, then first create a lookup relationship field after that change field type to Master detail relationship. This field type conversion can happen after providing the valid data into that field. For already existing records update this field either manually or Data Loader or ETL tools.
 
	If we want to convert Lookup relationship to master detail then provide the valid data in to the field and convert.
	If we want convert Master details relation to Lookup then if there is no rollup summary on master object then we can convert. If we have Roll up summary we can’t convert Master details to LookUp.
	







 Junction Object 

	Any object which have 2 master-detail fields from different objects then that object is called as Junction Object. It s the many-many relationship.
	The Owner of the primary master i.e the owner of the Junction object.
	In below example Course owner is the owner of the Student as well.
	

 

 




Hierarchical relation

In Lightning Goto Object manger-> User object and create the Hierarchical relation.
It is 1-1 Relation.

 





External Relation

	To create external relation ship first we need to create ‘External data Source’ and then validate and Sync the objects then it will create the External objects.  

Navigation in classic:
	Setup->Build->develop->Lightning comments-> External data sources.
Navigation in Lightning:
	Setup-> Platform tools->Integrations->External data sources.

	Once External objects Synced then we can create external relationship field in normal navigation.
	External data source URL for testing purpose.
https://orderdb.herokuapp.com/orders.svc/
	External object wiand then vall have Suffix of ‘__x’.  like Payments__x
 

               

