	If don’t create tab for the object then we can’t create a new record through UI since we can’t be able access the object in UI screen but we upload data using data Export, Dataloader.Io and other Tools.



 

 

 

 


 


Search Layout

	After clicking the object tabs what all the fields to display will organized by Search Layout.

 

To setup:
Search Lay out and edit respective Profile.

 
 
	Search results
 

	Lookup Filter and List view Options.
 


Below highlighted is the Example for List View
 



Page layout

	One profile will have one Page layout on each object.
	One-page layout can assign to one profile or many profiles.
	Every page layout will one Mini page layout. if we assign a page layout corresponding mini page layout will automatically assign.
	The page layout editor lets you:
o	Control which fields, lists of related records, and custom links users see
o	Customize the order that the fields appear in the page details
o	Determine whether fields are visible, read only, or required
o	Control which standard and custom buttons appear on records and related lists
o	Control which quick actions appear on the page
Wondering what the icons mean to the left of some of the field labels? 
•	 ―The field must have a value to save the record, but isn’t required on the page layout itself.
•	 ―The field must be included on the page layout because an administrator configured the field as universally required or Salesforce automatically requires the field. Although you can’t remove such fields, you can move them to different locations.
•	 ―The field is a controlling field.
•	 ―The field is a dependent field.
•	 ―The field is read-only.

	There are three primary types of custom buttons and links that you can create.
o	List button—Appears on a related list on an object record page.
o	Detail page link—Appears in the Links section of the record details on an object record page.
o	Detail page button—Appears in the action menu in the highlights panel of a record page.


 

Mini page layouts

	Every page layout will one Mini page layout. if we assign a page layout corresponding mini page layout will automatically assign.
	If we place cursor on the record then it will display the one page layout that is called Mini page layout.
 

	While creating Page layout we have option to edit Mini page layout in both classic and Lightning.
 

Record Types 

	Record types : Based on record type it will navigate to different screen and this different screens are created by using Page layout.




 
 

 


 

 
	Once record type created and assigned to particular profile we can’t delete or deactive them until we remove the default from the profiles. If we try to delete or deactivate it throw beloe error.
 
To change the default record type for the object follow below steps.
Go to profile and change the default record type to master in Record type setting.

 

After changes to master.
 

Now try to delete or deactivate the record type.
 

While deleting the existing record type we can chose to replace with other record type or with none for the existing records.

Compact page layouts  

	After clicking the any record in object the header part we call it as Compact layout.
	Compact layouts control which fields your users see in the highlights panel at the top of a record. They also control the fields that appear in the expanded lookup card you see when you hover over a link in record details, and in the details section when you expand an activity in the activity timeline.
	When you create a custom object, it’s automatically assigned to a system default compact layout, which has only one field on it: the object name.
 

Navigation Classic and Lightning:
Object manager select object click on Compact layoutcreate one and assign.

Related Lists

	It is one kind of section where we add related list in the Page layout section to display the related entries.
	Creation is same in both Classic and Lighting.
	Fields to display for related list we can set up after clicking the setting icon select fields to display.

 
List View

	For list view there is no option to create in Setup, we can only create after clicking tab.
The list of records to display based on filter is called as List view.

 

Navigation In Lightning:
->Click on setting icon on Tab then create a new list view.

 

