4)Managing data access

Trail Head: Profiles, data security, salesforce security guide, Field level security and Role hierarchy 
	If we want to check the record id of the User then go to the user and check the URL.
 

	Decide Who Can Use Lightning Experience
o	To use Lightning Experience, users must have the Lightning Experience User permission. This permission is automatically enabled in all standard Salesforce profiles. But custom profiles don’t usually include this permission by default. So we need to enable the ‘Lightning Experience User’ Permission.
	Enable Chatter Email Notifications: When you enable email notifications for Chatter, your users start receiving email notifications about new posts, comments, and other changes.

In the Setup Quick Find box, enter Email Settings, and then click Email Settings.


Profile

	Profile: It is a collection of settings and permissions.
1.	Standard profile: Any profile created by the Salesforce. We can’t delete standard profile. We can only modify.
2.	Custom profile: any profile created by the user.
	Go to users-> profiles->Created new profile by cloning the existing profile and then edit the permissions.
	If we enable ‘Developer Mode’ option in user setting then we can be able create VF pages classic environment itself.
	Profile can control which we can see
1.	Applications
2.	Objects
3.	Fields
4.	Tabs
5.	Page Layouts/Record Type
6.	Admin
7.	Used level access
8.	Security permissions 
9.	Login base on IP ranges
10.	Login Hours: If set login hours then profile assigned users can login only login hours.
11.	


 


 
 

 


 

 


 

 


Permission Set

	If we want to give any extra permissions to a specific user apart from what he getting from the 
Profile then we will go with the Permission set.
	Every permission set is created for specific license. In Permission set we can provide extra permissions based on Lenience only. If we want to assign the permission set then user and permission set both should have same license.
	In Permission sets, We can’t remove existing permissions that are getting from the profile, we can only provide extra permissions.
	Using permission set we can grant most of the permission’s that are available in Profile.

 

 

 
 
Navigation to assign permission set to user:
Setup->Administrate->manage users-> Users-> Click on user and then assign the permission set.
	MFA
o	To enable MFA for user we need to enabled the ‘Manage Multi-Factor Authentication in User Interface’  in profile or create the permission set. Also we have option for ‘Muti-factor authentication for API logins’.
o	Enable MFA for users by assigning the Multi-Factor Authentication for User Interface Logins user permission. You can do this step by editing profiles or by creating a permission set that you assign to specific users.
o	Normally we use the ‘Salesforce Authenticator App’.  After enabling the MFA for users, when first time login user can register to the App once after that user will get a notification every time login ‘ACCEPT/reject’. \;
o	In Mobile app if we enable ‘Always approve from this location’ then app will automatically approve the login request from this location login tried.
o	Any time user tries to log in from a different location, user can add the location to the Salesforce Authenticator list of trusted locations. To view the list and other account details, user selects the information icon which opens the accounts details page.
o	To check the History of MFA logins check under ‘Identity Verification History’.
o	
Roles Hierarchy
	Roles Hierarchy

    
 
 

 


 

User Management

	User management
 

	Who see what in salesforce OWD(Organization wide defaults):

 

	Every user will have one Role, Profile and Lenience.
	Once user created we can’t delete the user either we can deactivate or Freeze. 
	If we deactivate the user the assigned user license will be free and we use the license to created to new.
	If the user frizzed the assigned user license will still allocated the same user but he can’t login until we unfreeze the user.
	User level restriction 
1.	User deactivation: User level 
2.	User freeze : User level 

	Profile level User restriction
1.	Login IP set up in assigned profile
2.	Login Hours set up in profile (ex. If the login hours are set to 1 P.M to 6 P.M then user can be able to in the time only. One of user is logged in at 5.45 P.M then now the system time is 6.01 P.M then user can continue to work but he can’t relog in after 6 P.M) 
3.	Maximum invalid login attempts (we can reset the password or Unlock the user) 

	Organization level user restriction: If any third part is trying to connect salesforce its required username, password and Security token.
If we want to allow the trusted third party  with only user name and password then enable network access.

Setup-> Administrator->security Controls -> Network Access



 

	If the user trying to login but not able to login , administrator checked the login history but there is entry with error reason may be the Invalid User name. If the Username is valid then only entry will be updated in the Login History.
	With same email id we can create any number of users.


 

 

 


 

 


 

 

 

 

 


 

 

 



 


	Is set user same profile then those set of users have same license.
	Mange profiles and permission sets : option we enable to the particular profile then assigned profile users on created and edit profiles.
	Manges Users: id enable this option then only that profile users can create users
	Mange ip ranges:
	Manage business hours
	Rest passwords
	View SetupConfiguration: If we enable this option then only that assigned profile users can be able to see the ‘SETUP’ option.
	Customize Application: we need to enable this option in profile to create objects , reports, fields, tabs and workflow.


	If Admin want to login to any user without password we need to enable the ‘Admin can log in as any user’ Option.

Navigation:
->Adminster->Security Controls->Login access policies.

	Now Admin login as other user ‘A’ now if logout from user ‘A’ both admin and user ‘A’ sessions will logout if we enable ‘Force relogin after Login-As-User’. After logout from user ‘A’ session and the Admin still want login with the admin session  we need to disable this option.

->Adminster->Security Controls->Session setting

	Admin login as specific user that entry will be not be added in login history if we want to check that ‘View setup audit trails’.
->Adminster->Security Controls->View setup audit trails
	 

 

 
	Password policies: These are available at organization level and Profile level.

 
 




