5) Security
Security we have in 4 Levels
1)	Organization Level
a)	Password Policies
b)	Network access
c)	Authentications
d)	SSO
e)	Login hours

2)	Object Level Security
a)	Profile 
b)	Permission Set

3)	Record level Security
a)	OWD
b)	Role hierarchy
c)	Sharing Rule
d)	Manual Sharing
e)	Team Members
f)	Territories
g)	Profile Level
->View All, Modify all 
->View Alldata, Modify Alldata 
h)	Apex based sharing

4)	Field Level Security
a)	Profile
b)	Permission Set
c)	Page layout
d)	Record type

 


Object level security

	Object level security can be performed at 2 level
1)	At Profile level
2)	Permission set
 

 

Record level Security
In record level security can be controlled in different ways as below.
a)	OWD
b)	Role Hierarchies
c)	Sharing Rules
1)	Owner based sharing rules
2)	Criteria based sharing rules
3)	Manual sharing rules
4)	Apex based sharing rules
d)	Team Sharing
1)	Account Team
2)	Case Team
3)	Opportunity Team
e)	Territories
f)	Profile Level
1)	View All
2)	Modify All
3)	View All data 
4)	Modify All data
g)	Permission set
1)	View All
2)	Modify All
3)	 View All data 
4)	 Modify All data



 


 

 


OWD 

Navigation in Classic:
                  Setup->Administrate->Security Controls-> Sharing Settings
 Navigation in Lightning:
 	Setup->Security->Sharing Settings.

OWD: Organization wide default’s
	OWD Private Permission: Only Owner of the record can see the record and perform read, write, delete and transfer. 
	OWD public read: every user in organization can see every record. On own record he can perform R/W/D/T and on others records only read operation.
	OWD public read/Write: every user in organization can see every record. On own record he can perform R/W/D/T and on others records only read/Write operation.
	OWD public read/Write/transfer: every user in organization can see every record. On own record he can perform R/W/D/T and on others records only read/Write/transfer operation.
This option Available only for Lead/Case object only.
	OWD public Full access: every user in organization can see every record. On own record he can perform R/W/D/T and on others records only read/Write/transfer/delete operation. This option Available only for Campaign object only.
	Controlled by Parent: When two objects are connected by Master detail relationship then Child object will not have any owner field. OWD applied for Master object same OWD will applied for Child object as well which is called Controlled by parent. 



 
 


 

 


Role Hierarchies

	If we enable grant Access using Role Hierarchy option in sharing setting the people who are the above role to you, they can perform R/W/D/T operation.
	For all standard objects this option by default enable. For custom objects we need to enable manually.

 

Sharing Rules

	Sharing rules are used to grant extra permissions to a group of peoples Based business requirement. Whatever permissions we get through OWD we will get and extra permission we will get through Sharing rules.
	By sharing rules we can’t reduce the permission we can only able to give extra permissions.
These is same to permission sets only, but permission sets perform on object level and sharing rules on the record level.
	When OWD is private/Public read but we need to grant extra permission then will go for sharing rules.
	Using sharing rules we can’t share to a particular user either we can share with Role , Role& Sub and Public Group.
	At least one user does not have the R/W permission in organization then Sharing Button will visible in record. If we open any record in any object, sharing button not visible means every user in the Organization have the read/Write permission May be because of profile/Permission set/OWD/Sharing rules. If we click one the sharing button, then we can be able to see the who all are have the access to that record and the reason(OWD, Sharing rule or permission set or Team sharing or Territory).
	  We are 4 different type of sharing rules
1)	Owner based sharing rules
2)	Criteria based sharing rules
3)	Manual Sharing rules
4)	Apex based sharing rules
 
	As per the above example if we set OWD as Private then Owner of the records can only access the data as below.
Sam:C01, Ram:C02, Kiran:C03, Prasad: C04
Now our requirement to see the records as below then we go for the sharing rules.
Sam:C01, C02,C03
Ram:C01, C02
Kiran:C03
Prasad:C04, C03

	Queue: If you want a group people to be a owner we will go for concept of Queue. We c can’t be create queue on Account, Contact opportunity and User objects.
	We can create queue on every custom object.
	The members of the queue can perform Read/Write/Transfer only record. Can’t perform delete operation.

Navigation in classic:
	Setup->Administer-> Manage user->Queues 
	Navigation in Lightning:
	Setup->Administration ->users->Queues 
	Public Group: Group of users wrapped under one name. Public group can’t be owner of the record. If group is created by Admin, then it’s a Public group.
	Private Group: Group of users wrapped under one name. Private group can’t be owner of the record. If group is created by other than Admin(Any other user), then it’s a Private  group.

Navigation in classic: 
Setup-> Administer-> Manage Users-> Public Groups.

Navigation in Lightning:
	Setup->Administration ->users->Public groups 

Navigation in classic.
Setup-> Administer-> security Controls->Sharing Settings-> Go for the object and create a new rule.
Navigation in Lightning.
Setup-> Settings->Security-Sharing Settings-> Go for the object and create a new rule.

1)	Owner Based sharing rules
Owner based sharing rule will apply exist data and newly created data as well.

Use case:  In below hierarchy, HR execute data will visible to only HR manger not to the VP and CEO . 
Solution: If we enable Grant access using role hierarchy, HR execute data will visible to HR manger, VP and CEO as well. So, we need to disable to Gran access using role hierarchy and create sharing rule that HR executive role data share with HR Manger role then only HR manger role will able see the HR executive role data not be able see the VP and CEO role.

 

 

 

2)	Criteria Based sharing rules
We share the record based on conditions like only active records can share with either Role,
Role &Sub and public groups. 

3)	Manual Sharing
If you want to share any particular record, Go the record and click on the sharing button and then click ADD button then you can select Role, Role&Sub, Public group or you can share with a Particular group.
In Manual sharing only we share the record with a particular user.


Use case: By default, ‘Manual user Record sharing’ option is disabled so one user can’t edit other user details but they can see the user data. Suppose User B want to update the user A details in user setting. Fellow the below steps.

Before to the settings: There is no option to edit.

 


	Login to user ‘A’, go to sharing settings and enable the ‘Manual user Record sharing’ option. Now click on the user ‘A’ and click on sharing button then add user ‘B’ in the list.
 
Click Sharing Button.
 

Add the user in list.
 

	Now User ‘B’ can be able to edit the User ‘A’ details.
 

4)	Apex Based Sharing rule.
Wherever we can’t achieve the sharing using Owner based, Criteria and manual sharing then we will go the Apex based sharing rule(Programmatical ).




